#Text=Competing at the Eurovision in 1979 , you ended the voting on the wrong end of a close three-way finish , being beaten by the songs from Israel and Spain .
#Text=Considering your victory helped Luxembourg win twice in a row , were you happy for Israel as they also achieved the same feat ?
#Text=AMD
#Text=: Of course ! It 's once again a rule fixed ahead of time , and which does not prohibit a country from winning several times in a row .
#Text=( (
#Text=MH
#Text=) )
#Text=Many Eurovision fans on sites like YouTube feel the 1979 Contest was one of the strongest years ever for Eurovision .
#Text=Apart from your own song , were there any songs you remember that you really liked ?
#Text=Also , which song do you feel was a stronger entry , " Je suis l'enfant soleil " or " Tu te reconnaîtras " ?
#Text=AMD
#Text=: I have indeed seen how much Internet users appreciate " Je suis l'enfant soleil " ... let them be reassured , so do I !
#Text=That year , in 1979 , I particularly liked Milk and Honey and Gali Atari who won , and the German group who sang " Dschinghis Khan " , which was a very strong title and sold well .
#Text=With time , singing my songs from Eurovision continue to give me pleasure .

#Text=" Je suis l'enfant soleil " tells a very beautiful tale and allows me to play comedy [ Editor 's note : " Comedy " in the theatrical sense , aiming to denounce the faults and vices of society using humor ] a lot .
#Text=But I adore " Tu te reconnaîtras " for what it has in singing , pulling in , being direct with the audience .
#Text=In fact , each [ song ] brings me something different and to the public as well .
#Text=1980s : Retirement
#Text=( (
#Text=MH
#Text=) )
#Text=During the 1980s , you competed in some more song festivals , including one in Norway and one in Chile .
#Text=Anabela , the 1993 entrant from Portugal , felt she was eventually typecast as being " the song festival girl .

column1: #Text=I am currently preparing a song for my English[-language ] dance floor album ( yep ! ) which is being [ released ] by Energise Records . [ Dance music ] is totally the opposite of what I do ... but that amuses me and also the producers convinced me that I 'd be great in it ... so I hope not to disappoint them . [ Here 's a ] scoop : it 's called " You Came to Me .
